parameters:
Nora's oldest memory that she remembers. It was her walking
on a desolate beach. Unfamiliar scenery, unfamiliar smells,
everything was a mystery.

Above all, I couldn't remember my own name. Where I came
from, what I was, all of my memories had vanished.

The following year was a very difficult period for Nora. She
lived like a wild child, using the grasslands of the campus
as her hunting grounds. Memories that would never return,
they weighed heavily on her mind and body.

In the midst of all that, there were beasts in the campus
grasslands. Eventually, rumors spread and although they did
not participate in the war, nobles with strong ambitions for
fame began hunting with mercenaries under the name of beast
hunting.

Men chasing after her with unpleasant smiles. It was during
this time that Nora developed a discomfort towards men.

Nora, who had escaped by instinct, was finally captured and
restrained by the hands of nobles. She was fitted with a
muzzle and her hands and feet were immobilized with
restraints.

Nora, who possessed her original superhuman strength, should
have been able to easily destroy her restraints. However,
her fear of men, despair over her current situation, and the
endless days without a clear future had taken away all hope
for Nora to live.

My life doesn't matter anymore. That was Nora's only
emotion.
